==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muzarab
<hw>Muz"a*rab</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>mozarabe</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>mosta'rib</ets>, a name applied to
strange tribes living among the Arabs.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<def>One of a denomination of Christians formerly living under the
government of the Moors in Spain, and having a liturgy and ritual of
their own.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Mozarab</asp>,
<asp>Mostarab</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

